# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# @file        .github/CODEOWNERS
# @description Auto-review-assignment table for the Academorix frontend
#              monorepo. GitHub reads this file when a pull request is opened
#              and requests review from the LAST matching pattern for every
#              changed path. First non-matching commit gets no assignment.
#
# Semantics reminders (see https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositories-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners):
#   * Order matters — later patterns override earlier ones.
#   * Patterns use gitignore-style globbing (not glob(3)).
#   * `/foo/` matches only at the repo root; `foo/` matches anywhere.
#   * Team handles use `@org/team-slug`. GitHub silently drops patterns that
#     reference a non-existent user/team, which is why the placeholder team
#     `@academorix/platform-team` is documented — adjust the handle when the
#     GitHub organization + team are actually created.
#   * Branch-protection rules can require review from code owners; that is
#     what turns this file from documentation into an enforced gate.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Default owner — every path not matched by a later rule falls back here.
# Replace @academorix/platform-team with the real team slug once the
# GitHub org / team is provisioned.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
*   @academorix/platform-team

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Workspace root — turbo pipeline, pnpm workspace map, lockfile, top-level
# tsconfig, and every automation surface under `.github/` + `.kiro/`.
# Changes here alter how the entire monorepo builds, tests, and ships, so
# they always land on the platform team.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
/turbo.json                @academorix/platform-team
/pnpm-workspace.yaml       @academorix/platform-team
/pnpm-lock.yaml            @academorix/platform-team
/package.json              @academorix/platform-team
/tsconfig.json             @academorix/platform-team
/.github/                  @academorix/platform-team
/.kiro/                    @academorix/platform-team

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Applications — user-facing surfaces. Product-behaviour changes flow
# through the platform team until product-vertical teams exist.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
/apps/dashboard/           @academorix/platform-team
/apps/landing-page/        @academorix/platform-team

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Shared packages — every change to a package.json under packages/ affects
# every downstream consumer, so keep an explicit review requirement here
# even though it duplicates the default. This makes the intent readable
# to anyone browsing the file.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
/packages/analytics/          @academorix/platform-team
/packages/api-types/          @academorix/platform-team
/packages/core/               @academorix/platform-team
/packages/eslint-config/      @academorix/platform-team
/packages/feature-flags/      @academorix/platform-team
/packages/http/               @academorix/platform-team
/packages/i18n/               @academorix/platform-team
/packages/notifications/      @academorix/platform-team
/packages/pwa/                @academorix/platform-team
/packages/query/              @academorix/platform-team
/packages/realtime/           @academorix/platform-team
/packages/typescript-config/  @academorix/platform-team
/packages/ui/                 @academorix/platform-team

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Deployment surfaces — vercel.json per-app plus the workspace-level
# .vercel/ directory (project link + build settings). A misconfigured
# rewrite / header rule here can silently break production, so keep the
# gate explicit even though it is covered by the default.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
/apps/*/vercel.json        @academorix/platform-team
/.vercel/                  @academorix/platform-team
